 into built quality. This volume presents various ways to put construction works out to tender. In addition, it explains in practical terms how to describe construction work and how to prepare all of the documentation required for a complete invitation to tender.Subjects: Allocating construction work; Different ways to specify construction work; The structure of a work specification; Quantity determination; Using invitations to tender to realize plan quality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArchitecture. 0aConstruction contracts. 0aLetting of contracts. 4aArchitectural student handbook. 4aAward. 4aBasics series. 4aBid unit. 4aBuilding project. 4aBuilding quality. 4aBuilding service. 4aDrawing element. 4aItem. 4aPart lot. 4aProfessional practice. 4aRange of services. 4aService package. 4aTender specification. 4aTendering. 4aTextbook architecture. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh1 aFranssen, Sebastian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISHz978303561170008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062112908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z97831102385700 cEPUBz978303561267740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303561305640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035613056423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035613056/original  a978-3-0356-1170-0  BASICS ONLINE PACKAGE ENGLISH  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062112-9  DGBA Backlist Art and Ar